Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red-brown pottery vessel, interior slightly grooved, exterior partially smeared with resin, with remains of two lines of black-painted hieratic text on the exterior, with formula related to incense.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393128) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393128)
